Give an example of a historical event that demonstrates the power and influence of the Roman Empire.
The Pax Romana, or Roman Peace, was a period of relative stability and prosperity that lasted from around 180 AD to 235 AD during the reign of Emperor Antoninus Pius. This era, which saw the expansion of Roman culture and the spread of Christianity throughout the empire, is an excellent example of the power and influence of the Roman Empire.
